WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:08.420 --> 00:00:09.910
It is now my distinct pleasure to

00:00:11.600 --> 00:00:13.370
introduce our keynote speaker:

00:00:14.570 --> 00:00:15.440
business leader,

00:00:16.520 --> 00:00:17.720
investment icon,

00:00:18.890 --> 00:00:19.850
philanthropist,

00:00:21.570 --> 00:00:22.920
business school alum,

00:00:24.870 --> 00:00:26.220
university trustee

00:00:27.480 --> 00:00:29.250
and Carnegie Mellon champion

00:00:29.790 --> 00:00:31.410
David Alan Tepper.

00:00:43.030 --> 00:00:44.379
Oh, I have several pages to read,

00:00:44.590 --> 00:00:44.980
David.

00:00:47.950 --> 00:00:49.479
Through his legendary business

00:00:49.870 --> 00:00:50.440
savvy

00:00:50.970 --> 00:00:52.450
and investment expertise,

00:00:53.950 --> 00:00:56.140
David has earned an unrivaled

00:00:56.380 --> 00:00:57.969
reputation as one of the most

00:00:58.270 --> 00:01:00.009
successful hedge fund

00:01:00.220 --> 00:01:01.310
managers in the world.

00:01:02.860 --> 00:01:04.840
But he's equally well known

00:01:04.900 --> 00:01:05.790
for his passion

00:01:06.930 --> 00:01:07.860
for philanthropy.

00:01:09.290 --> 00:01:10.969
His belief in the power of higher
education,

00:01:10.970 --> 00:01:11.020
and,

00:01:12.470 --> 00:01:13.160
of course,

00:01:13.730 --> 00:01:14.569
his exceptional service

00:01:15.050 --> 00:01:16.789
and generosity to his

00:01:16.970 --> 00:01:18.679
alma mater Carnegie Mellon

00:01:18.920 --> 00:01:19.520
University.

00:01:20.910 --> 00:01:22.649
David grew up not too far from

00:01:22.890 --> 00:01:25.170
here in the Stanton Heights

00:01:25.260 --> 00:01:26.300
neighborhood of Pittsburgh.

00:01:27.380 --> 00:01:28.760
The middle of three children,

00:01:29.800 --> 00:01:31.470
I should just add that

00:01:31.960 --> 00:01:32.640
his mother,

00:01:33.180 --> 00:01:33.779
Roberta, is here

00:01:34.020 --> 00:01:35.639
with us. Would you please
acknowledge

00:01:36.210 --> 00:01:36.660
Roberta?

00:01:47.960 --> 00:01:49.199
He went to the University of
Pittsburgh

00:01:49.770 --> 00:01:51.900
for his undergraduate degree in
economics

00:01:52.890 --> 00:01:56.070
before receiving his MBA in 1982

00:01:56.580 --> 00:01:58.079
from our Graduate School of
Industrial

00:01:58.680 --> 00:01:59.490
Administration.

00:02:00.360 --> 00:02:02.210
It wasn't called the Tepper School
back there,

00:02:02.560 --> 00:02:03.230
I know.

00:02:04.560 --> 00:02:05.820
In 1985,

00:02:06.390 --> 00:02:08.310
he was recruited by Goldman Sachs

00:02:09.030 --> 00:02:10.260
as a credit analyst,

00:02:10.380 --> 00:02:11.940
and, within just six months,

00:02:12.600 --> 00:02:14.490
he became the head trader on

00:02:14.610 --> 00:02:16.280
their newly established high-yield

00:02:16.830 --> 00:02:17.520
bond group.

00:02:18.690 --> 00:02:20.250
This was the first clue

00:02:21.090 --> 00:02:22.100
that David was a force

00:02:23.040 --> 00:02:25.050
to be reckoned with on Wall Street.

00:02:26.160 --> 00:02:26.330
In 1993 — the

00:02:28.050 --> 00:02:29.880
same year the web

00:02:30.120 --> 00:02:31.040
entered the public domain — David

00:02:32.850 --> 00:02:34.830
established Appaloosa Management

00:02:35.150 --> 00:02:36.990
and, over the last 25 years,

00:02:37.380 --> 00:02:39.029
has built an impressively consistent

00:02:39.720 --> 00:02:41.040
record of high returns.

00:02:41.970 --> 00:02:43.079
Appaloosa currently has
approximately

00:02:43.800 --> 00:02:45.900
$17 billion under management

00:02:46.650 --> 00:02:48.329
and has yielded gross returns close

00:02:48.690 --> 00:02:50.100
to 40 percent per year

00:02:50.670 --> 00:02:52.080
over the past 20 years.

00:02:55.080 --> 00:02:56.820
Through the David

00:02:57.270 --> 00:02:58.280
Tepper Charitable Foundation,

00:02:59.610 --> 00:03:01.199
his philanthropy has expanded
opportunities

00:03:02.010 --> 00:03:02.790
for education,

00:03:03.780 --> 00:03:04.949
helped to fight hunger

00:03:05.460 --> 00:03:06.420
and homelessness,

00:03:07.140 --> 00:03:08.849
and provided much-needed disaster

00:03:09.420 --> 00:03:09.930
relief.

00:03:11.220 --> 00:03:12.809
He has generously donated a total

00:03:13.230 --> 00:03:15.090
of $125 million

00:03:15.630 --> 00:03:16.980
to Carnegie Mellon University,

00:03:24.390 --> 00:03:26.160
including naming

00:03:26.190 --> 00:03:28.440
and endowing the Tepper School of
Business,

00:03:28.890 --> 00:03:30.840
where he serves on the school's

00:03:31.110 --> 00:03:32.210
Business Board of Advisors.

00:03:33.710 --> 00:03:35.310
And in 2013,

00:03:36.330 --> 00:03:37.679
his most recent transformative

00:03:38.580 --> 00:03:39.959
gift enabled

00:03:40.560 --> 00:03:42.840
the creation of a state-of-the-art
facility

00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:44.655
on the new David A.

00:03:45.390 --> 00:03:46.340
Tepper Quadrangle,

00:03:47.550 --> 00:03:49.680
scheduled to open this fall.

00:03:54.870 --> 00:03:56.669
At more than 300,000 square

00:03:57.000 --> 00:03:58.409
feet, this building

00:03:58.920 --> 00:04:00.719
will serve as the new home for the
Tepper

00:04:01.080 --> 00:04:02.010
School of Business,

00:04:02.700 --> 00:04:04.410
as well as a major hub

00:04:05.130 --> 00:04:06.060
for collaboration,

00:04:06.900 --> 00:04:07.560
innovation,

00:04:08.250 --> 00:04:09.150
creativity

00:04:09.720 --> 00:04:11.670
and entrepreneurship at Carnegie
Mellon.

00:04:12.690 --> 00:04:15.630
Tepper Quad will create
unprecedented

00:04:15.900 --> 00:04:17.639
opportunities to break

00:04:17.940 --> 00:04:18.780
new barriers

00:04:20.110 --> 00:04:22.030
and to work toward new discoveries,

00:04:22.540 --> 00:04:23.590
new technologies,

00:04:23.830 --> 00:04:24.790
new businesses

00:04:25.360 --> 00:04:27.070
and new forms of expression.

00:04:28.390 --> 00:04:30.189
As our institution continues to

00:04:30.310 --> 00:04:31.989
grow and build for an evolving

00:04:32.560 --> 00:04:33.070
future,

00:04:33.995 --> 00:04:35.299
the Tepper Quad is the physical

00:04:35.960 --> 00:04:37.579
realization of a new

00:04:37.820 --> 00:04:39.610
model for 21st century research

00:04:40.040 --> 00:04:40.240
and education,

00:04:41.690 --> 00:04:43.009
and it will transform the CMU

00:04:43.550 --> 00:04:44.929
experience for generations

00:04:45.680 --> 00:04:46.670
of students to come.

00:04:47.960 --> 00:04:49.619
David has given so much

00:04:49.980 --> 00:04:50.820
to Carnegie Mellon,

00:04:51.690 --> 00:04:52.500
to our nation

00:04:52.650 --> 00:04:53.300
and the world,

00:04:53.970 --> 00:04:55.619
and we're delighted to welcome him
back

00:04:56.010 --> 00:04:57.719
to campus to share his

00:04:57.960 --> 00:04:58.530
wisdom

00:04:58.890 --> 00:05:00.820
with the Class of 2018.

00:05:01.170 --> 00:05:02.759
Please join me in extending a warm

00:05:03.150 --> 00:05:04.370
welcome to David A.

00:05:04.420 --> 00:05:04.920
Tepper. David.

00:05:14.310 --> 00:05:15.180
Good morning,

00:05:15.600 --> 00:05:18.440
Class of 2018.

