A kid,

00:12:39.510 --> 00:12:41.279
a kid who couldn't afford to

00:12:41.370 --> 00:12:42.630
go to an NFL game.

00:12:46.610 --> 00:12:46.660
A kid, a

00:12:49.460 --> 00:12:50.380
kid who —

00:12:51.320 --> 00:12:53.089
sorry about that — a kid who
couldn't

00:12:53.330 --> 00:12:54.770
afford to go to an NFL game

00:12:55.310 --> 00:12:56.750
until well into his 20s

00:12:57.260 --> 00:12:58.870
is on the verge of getting the NFL's
approval

00:12:59.600 --> 00:13:01.160
to buy the Carolina Panthers.

00:13:06.540 --> 00:13:07.410
Not too shabby,

00:13:09.780 --> 00:13:10.590
but believe me,

00:13:10.830 --> 00:13:12.000
it didn't start out that way.

00:13:14.010 --> 00:13:14.520
I grew up,

00:13:15.060 --> 00:13:16.709
I grew up in a working-class
neighborhood of Stanton

00:13:17.010 --> 00:13:18.270
Heights in the city of Pittsburgh.

00:13:19.110 --> 00:13:20.700
We played touch football in the
street

00:13:21.540 --> 00:13:23.550
and tackle football in a nearby
cemetery.

00:13:24.060 --> 00:13:25.490
We tried to not hit the gravestones.

00:13:27.200 --> 00:13:29.260
The cellphone of the day

00:13:29.890 --> 00:13:32.000
was mom calling up the street to say

00:13:32.050 --> 00:13:32.738
dinner was ready.

00:13:34.650 --> 00:13:36.050
My dad, like a lot of dads,

00:13:36.060 --> 00:13:37.739
had to work 60-hour weeks just

00:13:37.950 --> 00:13:38.770
to make ends meet.

00:13:40.610 --> 00:13:42.470
But he taught me a couple of things,

00:13:42.790 --> 00:13:44.140
a couple of important lessons.

00:13:45.200 --> 00:13:47.030
First, always think about charity

00:13:47.180 --> 00:13:48.380
and those less fortunate.

00:13:49.100 --> 00:13:50.690
He gave even when my family didn't

00:13:50.980 --> 00:13:51.680
have enough.

00:13:53.020 --> 00:13:54.840
And another lesson: He used to ask
us,

00:13:55.350 --> 00:13:56.310
"Who do you treat better,

00:13:57.270 --> 00:13:58.140
the president

00:13:58.680 --> 00:13:59.360
or the garbage man?"

00:14:01.100 --> 00:14:02.090
Do you guys know the answer?

00:14:03.660 --> 00:14:05.359
Garbage man? I'm talking just
generally

00:14:05.660 --> 00:14:07.400
— not about any specific president
by the way.

00:14:09.910 --> 00:14:10.570
Garbage man?

00:14:13.390 --> 00:14:13.870
Garbage man,

00:14:14.200 --> 00:14:16.090
garbage man may be the right answer
because somebody's

00:14:16.240 --> 00:14:17.460
got to take your trash every day,

00:14:17.470 --> 00:14:18.849
right? And if he doesn't take your
trash,

00:14:19.160 --> 00:14:19.560
you're really in trouble.

00:14:20.680 --> 00:14:22.000
But actually, the answer is

00:14:22.780 --> 00:14:24.450
you treat them both the same.

00:14:25.510 --> 00:14:26.350
All men

00:14:26.530 --> 00:14:27.430
and women,

00:14:28.270 --> 00:14:29.140
and women,

00:14:29.980 --> 00:14:31.540
deserve to be treated equally

00:14:31.600 --> 00:14:32.450
and with respect.

00:14:43.910 --> 00:14:45.890
Despite these good things about my
dad,

00:14:46.040 --> 00:14:47.020
he had a bad side, too.

00:14:50.940 --> 00:14:52.500
He was physically abusive to me.

00:14:54.030 --> 00:14:55.290
I'm sure it was a cycle

00:14:56.590 --> 00:14:57.970
that he got from his father,

00:14:58.810 --> 00:15:01.030
and his father got from his father.

00:15:03.190 --> 00:15:04.230
In my young life,

00:15:05.800 --> 00:15:07.340
there was nothing more terrifying.

00:15:08.720 --> 00:15:10.400
There is no greater adversity.

00:15:12.010 --> 00:15:13.060
But I prayed to God

00:15:13.990 --> 00:15:15.910
that I would never be the same to my
children.

00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:20.040
And I'm proud to say,

00:15:19.996 --> 00:15:21.630
in what I view as the

00:15:22.060 --> 00:15:23.409
greatest accomplishment of my life,

00:15:23.410 --> 00:15:23.460
I

00:15:25.660 --> 00:15:28.000
broke that cycle.

00:15:50.540 --> 00:15:50.910
Thank you.

00:15:53.510 --> 00:15:54.320
Now I'm shaking.

00:15:56.570 --> 00:15:58.329
High school was at an

00:15:58.420 --> 00:15:59.860
inner city school called Peabody.

00:16:00.450 --> 00:16:01.239
It was about half white

00:16:01.510 --> 00:16:02.830
and half African-American.

00:16:04.510 --> 00:16:06.000
There really was a lot of tension at
the school,

00:16:05.956 --> 00:16:07.599
between us at the school

00:16:07.810 --> 00:16:08.410
back then,

00:16:08.650 --> 00:16:10.000
and between the different high
schools.

00:16:11.080 --> 00:16:12.429
Things were so bad between
Westinghouse

00:16:13.000 --> 00:16:13.630
High School

00:16:13.810 --> 00:16:15.609
and Peabody — I think it's now
called a

00:16:15.670 --> 00:16:17.510
Barack Obama High — that

00:16:17.620 --> 00:16:19.350
when we played each other in
football it was

00:16:19.480 --> 00:16:21.249
in front of empty stands to keep

00:16:21.430 --> 00:16:22.300
people from fighting.

00:16:23.500 --> 00:16:24.160
It was rough.

00:16:24.950 --> 00:16:27.140
There was actually no

00:16:27.230 --> 00:16:27.829
grass on the field.

00:16:28.050 --> 00:16:28.820
It was dirt,

00:16:29.060 --> 00:16:29.630
rocks,

00:16:29.870 --> 00:16:31.850
and they used to oil down the field
to keep the

00:16:32.030 --> 00:16:33.050
dust from coming up.

00:16:33.740 --> 00:16:34.370
True story.

00:16:34.910 --> 00:16:36.730
One field goal post was against the
school.

00:16:37.760 --> 00:16:39.500
The other field goal post was
against a fence.

00:16:40.760 --> 00:16:41.956
If you ran out of the end zone,

00:16:41.990 --> 00:16:42.960
you had real problems.

00:16:45.640 --> 00:16:46.950
So I played a little football in
high school,

00:16:46.906 --> 00:16:48.800
and I was also in school plays,

00:16:49.410 --> 00:16:50.020
CFA.

00:16:52.050 --> 00:16:53.380
But money being short,

00:16:53.620 --> 00:16:54.310
I had a work.

00:16:55.710 --> 00:16:57.450
My first job application

00:16:57.540 --> 00:16:58.600
was at McDonald's.

00:16:59.160 --> 00:17:00.180
I got turned down.

00:17:01.960 --> 00:17:02.390
I did.

00:17:03.620 --> 00:17:05.570
I think it was because I had an
oversized

00:17:05.930 --> 00:17:06.410
Afro.

00:17:09.960 --> 00:17:10.580
Wouldn't be a problem today.

00:17:13.579 --> 00:17:14.520
I actually want to take it off,

00:17:14.476 --> 00:17:15.880
it was so frickin' hot up here,

00:17:15.910 --> 00:17:16.499
I gotta tell you.

00:17:18.220 --> 00:17:19.838
But I did get a job as a short-order
cook

00:17:20.109 --> 00:17:20.680
in a deli.

00:17:21.490 --> 00:17:22.440
I also sold knives door-to-door.

00:17:23.680 --> 00:17:25.210
And I was a union worker in a
bakery.

